<section xml:id="infinitelimits">
  <title>Infinite limits</title>
  <definition>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Let <m>(x_{n})</m> be a sequence of real numbers.
        <ol label="labelalph">
          <li>
            <p>
              We say <term><m>(x_{n})</m> tends to <m>\infty</m></term>
              or <term>diverges to</term>
              <m>\infty</m> or <m>x_{n}\rightarrow \infty</m> as
              <m>n \to \infty</m> if, for all <m>M>0</m>,
              there is <m>N</m> so that <m>n> N</m> implies <m>x_{n}\geq M</m>.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Similarly, we say <term><m>x_{n}</m> tends or diverges to <m>-\infty</m></term>
              or <m>x_{n}\rightarrow -\infty</m> as
              <m>n \to \infty</m> if, for all <m>M\lt 0</m>,
              there is <m>N</m> so that <m>n>N</m> implies <m>x_{n}\leq M</m>.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </statement>
  </definition>
  <example>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <m>\sqrt{n}\rightarrow\infty</m>:
        let <m>M>0</m>,
        we need to find <m>N</m> so that <m>n> N</m> implies <m>\sqrt{n}> M</m>.
        If we pick <m>N=M^2</m>, then for <m>n> N</m>,
        <me>
          \sqrt{n}> \sqrt{N}=\sqrt{M^2}=M
        </me>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Thus, we have shown that for any <m>M>0</m> we can find <m>N</m> so that <m>n> N</m> implies <m>\sqrt{n}\geq M</m>,
        hence <m>\sqrt{n}\rightarrow\infty</m>.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </example>
  <example>
    <statement>
      <p>
        The sequence <m>x_{n} = n^2-n-1</m> tends to infinity.
        To prove this,
        we must show that there is <m>N</m> so that <m>n> N</m> implies
        <me>
          n^2-n-1>M
        </me>,
      </p>
      <p>
        Note that for <m>n>1</m>,
        <me>
          n^2-n -1= n(n-1)-1\geq n\cdot 1-1=n-1
        </me>
      </p>
      <p>
        Thus, if <m>N=M+1</m>, then <m>n> N</m> implies
        <me>
          n^2-n-1 \geq n-1> N-1=M+1-1=M
        </me>.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </example>
</section>